✅ HOW TO RUN THIS ON UBUNTU (Step-by-Step)
1️⃣ Create a C file

Open terminal and type:

nano fileinfo.c


Paste the above code → save with CTRL+O, then exit CTRL+X.

2️⃣ Compile the program using gcc
gcc fileinfo.c -o fileinfo


If no errors → an executable fileinfo is created.

3️⃣ Run the program with multiple file names

Example:

./fileinfo fileinfo.c /etc/passwd /bin/ls


Example output:

File: fileinfo.c
Inode Number: 123456
File Type: Regular File

File: /etc/passwd
Inode Number: 890123
File Type: Regular File

File: /bin/ls
Inode Number: 456789
File Type: Regular File

✅ What examiners expect

This program covers:

✔ stat() system call
✔ st_ino (inode number)
✔ File type detection using macros
✔ Command-line arguments
✔ Loop for multiple files
